In article <9wRwgc1w165w@ephsa.sat.tx.us> jmm0021@ephsa.sat.tx.us (Jason Montgomery) writes:
>Ive seen lots of shows and books on the Encryption scemes that the 
>Germans and Japanese used during WWII.  What I am intrested in is what 
>did the Allies use to protect data.  Is this known or is it just another 
>NSA secret.
>
According to "The Ultra Secret", the Polish and British cryptanalysis
of Enigma led Winterbotham to get the British to use one-time pads.
I don't know what the Americans used for telegraphic traffic, but
the story of the Navajo code talkers role in voice communications
is very famous.  Kahn's "The Codebreakers" may say more. 


